# Tutorial 1
The base to any system is it's OS. As you saw in the Linux-basics doc we provided you guys, Linux is made up of many flavours.
For this tutorial, you and your team will each need to learn and then demonstrate how to set up a Virtual Machine(VM)

__Tasks:__
1. Download the iso file of your choice of Linux flavour (Make sure it is the terminal only version)
2. Install the OS on your VM created in VirtualBox
3. Install and run the fastfetch package and then take a screen shot of what your VMs display looks like
